title: For Sale:  WWII Japanese Type 95 NCO Sword
postcontent:
I have for sale a WWII issued Japanese type 95 NCO sword. It is an all original, complete, numbers matching real sword. Not a replica. I've been collecting over 10 years and letting go of some things. 

This type 95 was made between late 1938 up to mid 1941. Late 1938 they changed the tsuba or guard to the 9mm thick brass from the 11mm thick brass of the first issue. And then in mid 1941 they changed the guard to the black iron style. 

Has the aluminium tsuka or handle. These are machine made blades, not handmade and signed on tang. Has matching serial number on blade and scabbard throat. 

The Blade was made by the Nagoya arsenal. Two arsenals made the blades, a third kokura did not make any but was a supervising arsenal of the type 95 project and their mark will be found at times along with the nagoya or tokyo first arsenal. This blade and sword were made by nagoya and you can tell on them by when you read the serial number. when you read the number the cutting edge of blade is facing up and it faces down as you read number on the tokyo first blades. 

The Fuchi Stampings, the piece right under the guard is stamped with three symbols, Gifu, Nagoya and Kokura. Gifu is the corporate logo of the group within the arsenal, there were six of these altogether. This one is Gifu, Second is the Nagoya Arsenal stamping and third the Kokura arsenal stamping which sometimes accompanies. 

The blood fuller is full length and the tip is correct, scabbard is correct and the blade is in good shape. few small dark spots but overall nice shape. 

I know what they sell for, if you can get them for 200 at your local gun show then I would advise you to just go buy it there or buy it for 200 and sell it to me for 400. Double your money. I will not ship either. Face to face. I will meet in wisconsin rapids or stevens point, tomah, or mauston

 Call or text REDACTED anytime. Thank you.

title: For Sale:  1989 Colt Delta Elite 10mm (stainless government model) plus extras and ammo
postcontent: This is absolutely one of the best firearms I've ever had the honor of owning. It pains me to let it go but I have no choice. Its a 1911 style 10mm and being a Colt its basically top of the line. No major scratches only some slight holster wear. It has the solid trigger and military style hammer. Both sides of the black handle have the Delta symbol as does one of the three clips (the others have the Colt logo). Eight shot clips, very safe to carry with one in the chamber. Comes with a forward tilted (I believe its called FBI canter style) Tagua leather right handed holster, a right handed fobus holster a bianchi dual clip (single stack only) holster, a leg strapped thigh holster and a two gun shoulder holster that also holds two clips. Also with it are cleaning supplies includng a special dry lubricant for stainless guns, a couple tactical knives, and a brand new range bag for storage and transport. Ammo is included and is 100 wadcutter rounds (twenty of which are Buffalo Bore's) and 250 hollow points. Most are winchester silvertip, hornady's, and midway's but there's a handful or federal personal defense with a central pin and even a couple of the old original winchester black talons! Now I know you can get the newer delta's for about $850 (not stainless but black or blued...sorry but I'm color blind!) However being that mine is the older version and stainless it raises the value. I hope whoever buys this realizes what an amazing piece of machinery it is, its highly accurate (I avarage 3" groups at about 50ft.), beautifully simplistic and in my opinion one of the best handguns one can own. Whether its for concealed carrying, home defense or just a beautiful addition to a collector's shelf. Cash or moneygram. Only way I will take a check is if I go to the bank and it gets cashed before the transfer. No paypal, no credit cards and no trades. The price is negotiable within reason but please keep in mind these range from $850 up to $1400 depending on the finish and year made, if you're gonna offer half don't bother...its a waste of both our time. I don't expect this item to stay listed very long as.   these particular models are fairly difficult to find.
